{"key":"processedPost-10575931","value":{"id":10575931,"first":10575890,"last":10587250,"when":1246032171,"utime":"06/26/09 07:02 PM","content":"I can't say plainly enough how much I hate the process of using a spoon to get spawn out of a jar.&nbsp; The spoon cuts many of the grains in half, leaving the uncolonized center of the grains exposed to mold spores.&nbsp; <br />Instead, I suggest banging the jar against a tire, phone book, or block of wood to break up the individual grains, and then simply pour them out.<br />Bulk substrates need not be sterile, nor do you need to spawn in sterile conditions.&nbsp; I doubt that was the problem.&nbsp; Either your spawn was contaminated from the get-go, or you damaged the grains when you spooned them out and that's where the contamination got its foothold.<br />I'm sure others will come along and say they've used a spoon before with no problems, but I stand by the above.<br />RR","title":"Re: Bulk Tub Contammed, Help with procedure please"}}